text: ...Are you kidding me? Are they even trying anymore? For those of you that didn't read the original Mary Shelly's Frankenstein, it contained NONE of this shit. Hell, it barely even seems to connect with the concept of the Frankenstein Monster at all. The book was simply a back-and-forth perspective switching between the monster and the doctor, then stuff happens. This crap about "Demons" and "Magic" was not there in the book. I'm still waiting for a true adaptation of the book, not this sequel, "based on" crap that is using the book's name for bonus marketing. If you wanna create an extra storyline to a well-renowned literature piece, then fine, go all out. But this trailer looks like its flat out using Frankenstein's name for a quick extra buck, not an actual continuation. Hell, it's not even set in the same time period, NOR the place of which the book took place the most.

Epic isnt the overuse of farty dubstep, orchestral music, flashing editing, mugging actors and cgi-feasts. Give me a 65million dollar budget I will show people epic, an epic that will last for all time..

text: For everyone's information, this isn't based on Mary Shelley's novel. It's not even in the same universe. It's based on a graphic novel. But from what I get, this is an entirely different take on the story and the "monster" adopts the name of his creator (you know, Victor Frankenstein).
